    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-19T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/989: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-19T17:00:00-03:00"
                            >August 19, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191. Embassy’s 182, August 3, noon. The Embassy is informed by Sebastian
                        Sampaio<note n="10" xml:id="d326fn10">Chief of the Commercial Section of the
                        Ministry for Foreign Affairs.</note> that the assurance contained in the
                    above-mentioned telegram had been given in accordance with information received
                    from Raul Fernandez, Government leader in Chamber. Mr. Sampaio now doubts that
                    the agreement can be ratified by the end of August although he is still certain
                    that it will eventually be ratified. He explains that the unforeseen delay is
                    due to the fact that the Finance Committee has unexpectedly refused to vote on
                    the trade <pb facs="0401" n="308" xml:id="pg_308"/> agreement until it has been
                    reported by the Committee of Commerce, Industry and Agriculture.</p>
                <p>The agreement must also pass the Senate.</p>
                <p>I shall call the Department’s telegram 124, July 24, 6 p.m., to the Ambassador’s
                    attention immediately upon his return next Thursday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
